    It is difficult to explain why a specialist in the history of religions, living in Quebec, accepted to join the AIME project. As it happens, it is partly due to the fact that Milad, an historian and specialist in ancient texts has become one of the most listened commentators on the changes taking place in digital cultures. It is thus an enormous opportunity for the project to benefit from not only from his keeping a watchful eye on the content but also on the project’s modus operandi. He will be helping the participants to modify the system so as to take maximum advantage of the power of those digital worlds placed at the service of this odd inquiry.

